Since universal elements are terminal, the limit \operatorname *{lim} D\xrightarrow {\lambda } D of a
  diagram J\xrightarrow {D} C is terminal in the category of
  elements \text {el}(\operatorname *{Cone}_D), in the sense that for any other cone
  c\xrightarrow {\mu } D, there exists a unique map c\to \operatorname *{lim} D so that each of
  the following triangles commute:




